  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated WASH and Agriculture Project (IWAP)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Construction of water infrastructure e.g. sand dams, roof rain water harvesting systems in institutions, drilling boreholes, water kiosks and pipeline extensions. 

 Capacity building of water management committees 

 Distribution of dry land pulse to farmers and extension services support to farmers. 

 Sanitation and hygiene promotion through CLTS approach 

  Capacity building of partner staffs and farmers on Community Managed Disaster Risk Reduction approaches</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Households have improved livelihoods security, increased access to water for multiple uses, increased resilience to climate change impacts on unpredictable rainfall and floods</narrative>
  </description>
